<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-046-088 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 498 668</DOCID><JOURNAL>Industrial Engineering  Oct 1991 v23 n10 p16(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Simulation model's level of detail determines effectiveness.andO;(Simulation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Law, Averill M.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Determining the level of detail in a simulation of a process isessential in order to yield credible results and to reduce wasteof computing resources and time.andP;  A simulation should containenough elemental detail to address the issues being investigated.andO;One-to-one elemental correspondence is not always required.andO;Sometimes certain elements of the systems need not be included inthe simulation model because their inclusion may not affect theresults of the study.andP;  If there is a lack of detail, however, theresults can be faulty.andP;  The issues of a study should be clearlydefined at the outset of a simulation project.andP;  Experts alsoshould be included in determining the scope of a simulation.andO;Sensitivity analysis is important because it provides a method ofdetermining an element's effect on the whole system.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     SimulationModelingData AnalysisSensitivity Analysis.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>